name: nytimes
text: SpaceX tested a prototype of its Starship rocket on Wednesday, which ended in a fiery blast. The test was partly successful, and the company described it as “awesome” despite the explosion. https://t.co/wrPJ6J4o7G

text:

name: nytimes
text:
Rudy Giuliani became the latest in President Trump’s inner circle to boast about the treatment he received for Covid-19. The access given to Trump and his allies is raising alarms among medical ethicists as hospitals across the country ration care.

text: A SpaceX Starship prototype, a rocket Elon Musk envisions ferrying humans to Mars, exploded on Wednesday while attempting to land during a test. https://t.co/banViluER7 https://t.co/oUR7L0tTFK

name: nytimes
text:
At least 356,000 more people than normal have died in the U.S. between March 15 and Nov. 21 according to our analysis of data from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

That is nearly 20% higher than what would be expected in a normal year. https://t.co/MikvQt4yqb

name: nytimes
text: Deaths nationally are higher than they would be in a normal year, with 21 states currently hitting peak numbers of… https://t.co/zgCSktnrR4

name: nytimes
text:
Our analysis examines deaths from all causes and includes deaths related to pandemic-related disruptions as well as the virus itself. 

Epidemiologists refer to the deaths in the gap between the observed and normal numbers of deaths as “excess deaths.” https://t.co/MikvQt4yqb https://t.co/Vq9QyXZgMk

name: nytimes
text:
From March 15 through Nov. 21, the most recent date with reliable statistics, excess deaths were 39% higher than the official coronavirus fatality count. If this pattern held through Dec. 9, the total death toll would be over 400,000.

See our analysis: https://t.co/MikvQt4yqb
